Interface FitnessFunction

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DeJong, HyperEllipsoid, Rastrigin, RosenbrocksValley, Schwefel

    public interface FitnessFunction
    Interface for the fitness functions applied to each of the five benchmark functions that are evaluated

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.Double evaluate(Vector vector)
      Evaluates the fitness of the benchmark function and returns the fitness value.
      com.google.common.collect.Range<java.lang.Double> getBounds()
      Returns the bounds for the benchmark function that is being evaluated.
      java.lang.String getName()
      Returns the name of the fitness function, this is useful for plotting the fitness results and saving the image as the name of the fitness function.
      java.lang.Integer getNFC()
      Returns the number of function calls (NFC) this is a count of the number of times the fitness function has been called.
      void resetNFC()
      Resets the NFC count, this is useful when running multiple new instances of the DE algorithm and you wish to reset the NFC.
